                    "body": "A \"quick and dirty\" fix would be to special case tables with zero rows and zero columns in the check in {{_reconstruct_index}} ([https://github.com/apache/arrow/blob/982f341bc81e1e22d4b25f8cf00ef882a34766b6/python/pyarrow/pandas_compat.py#L695-L697]), when recreating the pandas DataFrame from an empty arrow Table. \r\n\r\nBut I think the proper fix to this would be to allow the Table to have a non-zero {{num_rows}}. However, this would need separate fixes depending on where the Table is created (so eg a separate fix in the {{Table.from_pandas(columns=[])}} and the parquet read code, for both examples above), and complicate the code in several places, so I am not sure we want to go down that route. (cc [~wesmckinn] ?)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
